  "exploit_path": {
    "summary": "The attack was initiated from address 0x00c0F54D8Afc60F3aCd06E476Cf504A6f7f06180 via transaction 0x8580825008800b9e13266f40b41a838a521e4d0bb4abc1cb78684253b7bc9fd1. The attacker leveraged batch transaction capabilities to manipulate BGM's internal price feeds, likely exploiting insufficient price oracle safeguards or lack of TWAP (Time-Weighted Average Price) implementation. By executing coordinated trades within a single transaction batch, the attacker was able to artificially inflate or deflate asset prices to their advantage, extracting approximately $450,000 worth of value from the protocol. The attack pattern follows classic price manipulation vectors seen in similar DeFi exploits where pricing logic fails to account for within-block price manipulation.",
